### Is this a regression?

<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->
Yes, the previous version in which this bug was not present was: 9.1.11

### Description

I have multiple polyfills files I import in the polyfills.ts file. While using ng serve this works fine but when I build the application to prod it doesn't. The work around I found was adding the code block inline but is working fine in the previous version of angular, this stopped working when I created a new app with angular 10.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

I have this file: string.polyfills.ts
`
interface String {
    contains(search: string): boolean;
}
if (!String.prototype.hasOwnProperty('contains')) {
    String.prototype.contains = function (search: string): boolean {
        return this.indexOf(search) !== -1;
    };
}
`

and in the src/polyfills.ts line 55 I have the following
`import './path/to/string.extension';`

If I do ng serve I can do in the browser's console 'test'.contains(es);
But with ng serve --prod (for example) the string.contains is undefined.

If I add all the content of the file (string.polyfills.ts) in the polyfills.ts it works but I would like to know what it stoped working in angular 10.


