### Is this a regression?

Yes, this worked prior to Angular 10.


### Description

When building with --prod or anything else that has optimization: true, we get e.g. "this.$rawChange.startWith is not a function"
This is the same for all RXJS operators when trying to apply them to EventEmitters.

When building without --prod (or with optimization: false in the prod config) this works fine.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
Define an observable via. e.g. `new EventEmitter<string>()`; then try and use .startWith or any other operator.
This runs fine with optimizations disabled, and fails with optimizations enabled.

export class MyComponent implements OnInit {
$rawChange = new EventEmitter<string>();

ngOnInit() {
this.filteredOptions = this.$rawChange
      .startWith(startingWith || null)
      .map(valueChange => valueChange ? this.filter(valueChange) : this.options.slice());
}
}



## üî• Exception or Error
<pre><code>
this.$rawChange.startWith is not a function
</code></pre>


